n.%20Those%20were%20the%20films%20I%20loved.%20Those%20were%20the%20filmmakers%20I%20loved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Sebasti%C3%A1n%20Silva%2C%20who%20made%20%26quot%3BCrystal%20Fairy%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20had%20seen%20his%20film%20a%20couple%20years%20before%20at%20Sundance%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Maid%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWow.%20If%20people%20are%20making%20movies%20like%20this%2C%20I%20might%20want%20to%20try%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20this%20Hollywood%20thing.%26quot%3B%20It%20only%20made%20sense%20that%20I%20would%20sort%20of%20test%20out%20the%20waters%20in%20the%20independent%20film%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20television%20was%20a%20very%20exciting%20place%20at%20the%20time%2C%20so%20those%20two%20worlds%20felt%20like%20the%20proper%20stomping%20grounds%20for%20me%20to%20go%20and%20get%20my%20feet%20dirty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20your%20re-entry%20into%20Hollywood%20around%202013%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20media%20coverage%20of%20your%20return%20%E2%80%94%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20profile%20of%20you%2C%20and%20then%20press%20for%20%26quot%3BCrystal%20Fairy%26quot%3B%20with%20Michael%20Cera%20at%20Sundance.%20What%20did%20it%20feel%20like%20to%20have%20your%20return%20to%20acting%20be%20met%20with%20so%20much%20coverage%20and%20interest%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20didn't%20realize%20it%20was.%20I%20don't%20know.%20I%20wasn't%20paying%20attention%20to%20that%2C%20I%20guess.%20I%20was%20just%20relieved%20to%20be%20having%20an%20experience%2C%20an%20internal%20experience%20with%20myself%20that%20felt%20good%2C%20because%20I%20had%2C%20for%20many%20years%2C%2015%20maybe%2C%20not%20been%20acting%20in%20any%20significant%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20a%20couple%20of%20things%20here%20and%20there%2C%20but%20I%20left%20acting%20to%20go%20to%20college%20when%20I%20was%2017%2C%20and%20I%20never%20thought%20I%20would%20return.%20I%20spent%20a%20decade-plus%20after%20college%20really%20confused%2C%20an