%20started%20drinking%20heavily%20because%20I%20was%20so%20burned%20out%20at%20work.%20Quitting%20was%20the%20only%20way%20out.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221726%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shelley%20Paxton%2C%20a%20woman%20smiling%20in%20a%20cheetah%20print%20jacket%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6656eb38d38d94707c2be9b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221259%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShelley%20Paxton%20was%20the%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20at%20Harley%20Davidson%20but%20suffered%20from%20severe%20burnout.%3Cp%3ELena%20Jackson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EShelley%20Paxton%20learned%20that%20success%20meant%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20from%20a%20young%20age.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20developed%20an%20unhealthy%20relationship%20with%20work%20during%20her%20career%20as%20a%20marketer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPaxton%20became%20severely%20burned%20out%20as%20an%20executive%20and%20had%20to%20quit%20to%20overcome%20her%20health%20problems.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Shelley%20Paxton%2C%20an%20author%2C%20speaker%2C%20and%20coach%2C%20about%20her%20experience%20with%20professional%20burnout.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20middle-class%2C%20straight-laced%20family%20but%20always%20felt%20restless.%20I%20was%20raised%20primarily%20in%20Minneapolis%2C%20which%20felt%20very%20homogenous.%20I%20always%20wondered%20what%20else%20was%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20graduated%20from%20high%20school%2C%20I%20went%20to%20Boston%20College.%20I%20felt%20drawn%20to%20the%20East%20Coast%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20in%20a%20place%20with%20lots%20of%20diversity.%20Moving%20to%20Boston%20was%20one%20step%20toward%20broadening%20my%20worldview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fa250ca-6505-43b6-b333-6859bb895607%5C%22%3ESuccess%20meant%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20to%20the%20top%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20college%2C%20I%20started%20working%20as%20an%20assistant%20account%20executive%20in%201992%20in%20Chicago%20at%20a%20huge%20global%20advertising%20agency%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ddb.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDDB%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20followed%20in%20my%20dad's%20footsteps%20as%20a%20marketer.%20He%20worked%20on%20many%20cool%20brands.%20I%20watched%20him%20work%20his%20way%20up%20in%20his%20career%20to%20become%20the%20CEO%20of%20Hagen%20Dazs%20eventually.%20He%20made%20the%20script%20of%20success%20clear%3A%20climb%20every%20rung%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%20work%20for%20sexy%20brands%2C%20and%20get%20bigger%20and%20bigger%20titles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20rebellious%20growing%20up%2C%20but%20now%20I%20can%20see%20that%20his%20career%20path%20influenced%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2026%2C%20I%20was%20successful%20in%20my%20career%20and%20had%20an%20active%20social%20life.%20I'd%20even%20taken%20a%20four-month%20sabbatical%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bsoulbbatical%26quot%3B%20as%20I%20call%20them%20now%2C%20to%20travel%20Europe.%20In%20my%20journals%20from%201996%2C%20I%20talked%20about%20following%20the%20winds%20of%20my%20soul%20and%20the%20tensions%20I%20felt%20in%20my%20career%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20who%20to%20talk%20to%20about%20my%20doubts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20solution%20was%20to%20move%20to%20Istanbul%20for%20an%20international%20role%20at%20the%20agency%20I%20was%20working%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20took%20this%20role%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20different%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20process%20that%20desire%2C%20so%20I%20stuffed%20it%20back%20down.%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20achieve%20a%20corporate%20career%20and%20travel%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reach%C2%A0success%20the%20Shelley%20Paxton%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20returned%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%202000%20to%20take%20a%20senior%20role%20at%20AOL.%20I%20then%20continued%20to%20work%20in%20marketing%20roles%20with%20large%20clients%20like%20Visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22766c9992-904c-4db0-bb1f-c065ac2bb3fb%5C%22%3EI%20wanted%20to%20rebrand%20myself%20after%20a%20divorce%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Harley%20Davidson%20hired%20me%20as%20VP%20of%20Global%20Integrated%20Marketing%20and%20Planning%20in%202010%2C%20I%20was%2040%20and%20had%20just%20gone%20through%20a%20very%20traumatic%20divorce.%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20life%20was%20upside%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarley%20Davidson%20was%20my%20first%20opportunity%20to%20work%20on%20the%20client%20side%20of%20marketing%2C%20not%20the%20agency%20side.%20I%20saw%20myself%20as%20a%20biker%20babe%20marketer%20for%20one%20of%20the%20most%20iconic%20motorcycle%20brands%20on%20the%20planet.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BHell%20yes%2C%20I%20want%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20the%20role%20would%20be%20my%20chance%20for%20reinvention%2C%20but%20ultimately%2C%20it%20was%20my%20final%20lesson%20and%20wake-up%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22744e880b-56bd-49ea-aa2f-33016d744ceb%5C%22%3EIf%20I%20wasn't%20working%2C%20who%20would%20want%20me%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20struggled%20throughout%20my%20career%20with%20prioritizing%20work%20over%20my%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20an%20unfortunate%20pattern%20for%20me.%20Back%20in%202006%2C%20I%20agreed%20to%20go%20to%20Shanghai%20for%20a%20work%20assignment%20for%20Omnicom%20Media%20Group.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20my%20now%20ex-husband%20and%20I%20were%20trying%20to%20have%20children%20and%20wanted%20stability.%20Instead%20of%20honoring%20that%2C%20I%20said%20yes%20to%20the%20assignment%20because%20I%20feared%20the%20company%20would%20no%20longer%20see%20me%20as%20valuable%20if%20I%20said%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20believed%20that%20if%20I%20didn't%20put%20work%20first%2C%20Harley%2C%20or%20any%20company%20I%20worked%20for%2C%20wouldn't%20want%20me%20anymore.%20And%20who%20would%20I%20be%2C%20then%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20allowed%20my%20entire%20sense%20of%20self%20and%20self-worth%20to%20be%20tied%20to%20my%20job%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20dangerous%20place%20to%20be.%20I%20always%20put%20work%20over%20my%20well-being%20and%20wasn't%20good%20with%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pattern%20became%20more%20unhealthy%20at%20Harley%20Davidson.%20I%20was%20working%20late%2C%20canceling%20social%20plans%20to%20work%20more%2C%20and%20constantly%20checking%20my%20work%20emails%20or%20taking%20calls%20after%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22403172a7-96a7-4167-bfc4-76cab3b5027b%5C%22%3EI%20had%20the%20role%20of%20a%20lifetime%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20feel%20happy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20had%20taught%20me%20to%20climb%20all%20the%20rungs.%20He%20was%20telling%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20be%20the%20president%20of%20Harley%20Davidson.%20You've%20got%20this.%20Keep%20going.%20Keep%20climbing.%26quot%3B%20But%20I%20realized%20I%20didn't%20want%20that%20%E2%80%94%20even%20when%20I%20was%20promoted%20to%20CMO%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20exhausted%20and%20burned%20out%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20guilty%20that%20I%20wasn't%20happy%20in%20my%20new%20role.%20It%20was%20a%20marketer's%20dream%20job%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20privileged%20even%20to%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20this%20all%20there%20is%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202015%2C%20I%20started%20having%20vivid%20recurring%20nightmares%20about%20my%20dog%2C%20who%20had%20died.%20In%20my%20dream%2C%20I%20neglected%20my%20beloved%20companion%2C%20and%20my%20dog%20had%20become%20emaciated%2C%20and%20I'd%20been%20too%20busy%20to%20notice.%20Shortly%20after%2C%20I%20started%20drinking%20heavily%20to%20cope%20with%20the%20stress%20and%20help%20myself%20fall%20asleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20able%20to%20function%20while%20drinking%20one%20or%20two%20bottles%20of%