ion%20Americans%20ages%2055%20to%2064%20were%20holding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-issues-debt-relief-broken-industry-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudent%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20had%20spouses%20with%20loans.%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20boomers%20are%20also%20set%20to%20be%20saddled%20with%20that%20debt%20for%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20the%20burden%20of%20that%20debt%20appears%20to%20fall%20disproportionately%20on%20the%20lowest%20earners.%20Looking%20at%20debtors%20over%20the%20age%20of%2055%2C%20the%20Schwartz%20Center%20calculated%20that%20just%203.7%25%20were%20in%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20earners%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20or%20those%3Cspan%3E%20making%20more%20than%20%24192%2C000.%20Conversely%2C%20it%20found%2050.3%25%20were%20in%20the%20bottom%20half%20of%20earners%2C%20making%20below%20%2454%2C600%2C%20and%2046%25%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ein%20between%2C%20%3Cspan%3Emaking%20%2454%2C600%20to%20%24192%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20found%20that%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20younger%20boomers%20still%20expected%20their%20student%20debt%20to%20loom%20well%20into%20retirement%20age%3B%20on%20average%2C%20respondents%20to%20the%20Fed's%20survey%20ages%2055%20to%2064%20said%20they%20expected%20it'd%20take%2011%20years%20to%20repay%20their%20loans%2C%20meaning%20many%20would%20be%20saddled%20with%20that%20debt%20well%20into%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20older%20Americans%20already%20find%20themselves%20living%20off%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-poverty-older-americans-savings-inequality-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20than%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereliant%20on%20Social%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20to